# Airtable Configuration
# Get these values from your Airtable account:
# 1. Go to airtable.com and sign up (free)
# 2. Create a new Base called "Judo Classes"
# 3. Create a table called "Classes" with these fields:
#    - day (Single line text, e.g., "Monday")
#    - time (Single line text, e.g., "7:00 pm")
#    - endTime (Single line text, e.g., "8:30 pm")
#    - program (Single line text, e.g., "Adult Beginner Course")
#    - category (Single select: "kids" or "adults")
#    - ageGroup (Single line text, e.g., "18+" or "Ages 4–7")
#    - level (Single line text, e.g., "Beginner")
#    - status (Single select: "available", "limited", "enrolling")
#      → Only used when capacity is blank. Set manually if you don't want auto-status.
#    - duration (Single line text, e.g., "90 min")
#    - capacity (Number, optional)
#      → Max spots for this class. When set, the site computes status automatically:
#         ≥ 40% spots remaining  →  Available
#         < 40% spots remaining  →  Limited
#         0 spots remaining      →  Full
#      → Counts only non-cancelled bookings from the Bookings table (matched by Day + Class).
#      → Phone/WhatsApp bookings won't be counted unless manually added to the Bookings table.
#      → Leave blank to use the manual "status" field instead.
#
# 4. Create a table called "Bookings" with these fields:
#    - Name (Single line text)
#    - Email (Email)
#    - Phone (Phone number)
#    - Day (Single line text)
#    - Time (Single line text)
#    - Class (Single line text)  ← must match the "program" value in the Classes table exactly
#    - Age Group (Single line text)
#    - Category (Single line text)
#    - Status (Single select: "New", "Confirmed", "Cancelled")
#    - Submitted At (Date)
#
# 5. Get your Base ID from the URL: https://airtable.com/app/[BASE_ID]/...
# 6. Get your API key: Account settings → API → Personal access tokens

AIRTABLE_TOKEN=your_personal_access_token_here
AIRTABLE_BASE_ID=your_base_id_here

# Email Service (Optional - for booking confirmations)
# Choose one: Resend, SendGrid, Nodemailer, etc.
# RESEND_API_KEY=your_resend_api_key_here
